        <abstract>
            <p>Cannot accept JJW’s invitation to a party. His health has been worse than usual for some months – can see no one nor can he go anywhere.</p> 
<p>Is preparing a cheap edition of the <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi> [6th] and will answer Mivart’s objections.</p>  
<p>CD is pleased JJW likes C. Wright’s "Darwinism" [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">7940</hi>]. Huxley will publish a splendid review of it in <hi rend="italic">Contemporary Review</hi> [Nov 1871].</p> 
        </abstract>
